<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-19T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="917" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d917">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.7961/10: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-19T19:00:00-05:00">February 19, 1929—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>27. Department’s 16, February 16, 7 p.m. I have before me copy of
                            telegram from Minister for Foreign Affairs to Olaya authorizing him to
                            sign as desired by the Department with one slight addition after words
                            Colombian ports “where there are authorities charged with carrying out
                            the pertinent regulations.”</p>
                        <pb facs="1026" n="882" xml:id="pg_882"/>
                        <p>Olaya authorized to annex as Colombian regulations of [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] the “exact copy” of those presented by the Department as
                            “at present we have no especial legislation on the subject.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>